  "text": "It is of interest to estimate β * = max {β 1 , |β n−1 |} as this quantity can be used to bound the r -step distance to stationarity. For example, when K is reversible with respect to π, letting K r x denote the distribution of X r given that X 0 = x, we have the classical bound on the total variation distance to stationarity [CITATION_1] ",
